# CropAbility Python rules

## Publishable package

- **Only** `cropability` is installed (`pyproject.toml`: `include = ["cropability*"]`).
- Entry point: `cropability = cropability.cli.main:main`.
- Do not add sibling packages under `src/main/python/`.
- Legacy PGL remains in `archive/legacy/pgl/` — never move into the install tree.

## Layering

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `gpu/`, `kernels/` | PyTorch / Triton GPU compute |
| `genomics/` | GPU genomics (variant, LD, GWAS, alignment) — **not** CPU NGS |
| `ngs/` | Thin facade → `cropability.native._core` |
| `viz/` | Plotting only |
| `cli/` | User-facing subcommands |
| `utils/` | Config, logging, timers |
| `native/` | Import `_core` (maturin-built) |

## Forbidden in Python product code

- TorchScript export modules or CLI `export` for `.pt`
- Duplicating pileup/VCF/FASTA CPU logic (belongs in Rust)
- Full Python fallback when `_core` is missing (document maturin build instead)

## Imports (preferred)

```python
from cropability.ngs import VariantPipeline, FastaReader
from cropability.gpu import get_device_manager
from cropability.kernels.seq import encode_sequences
```

Deprecated shims (`cropability.io`, `cropability.genomics.pipeline`) — touch only to maintain re-exports.

## Optional extras

`[gpu]` triton · `[io]` pysam/biopython · `[rust]` maturin · `[viz]` matplotlib/seaborn/plotly

## Tests for changes

Add or update tests under `src/test/python/` per `doc/TESTING.md` — not under `scripts/`.
